##### hostPath Volume ##########
hostPath mounts node filesystem into Pod.

@@ Architecture:

Worker Node
  |
/data
  |
Pod

@@ Example:

volumes:
- name: host-storage
  hostPath:
    path: /data
volumeMounts:
- mountPath: /host-data
  name: host-storage

@@ Verify:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl exec -it hostpath-demo -- ls /host-data

You will see node files.

@@ Why hostPath is Dangerous ?
Pod gets access to Node Filesystem

@@ Potential risks:
Security Issues
Node Manipulation
Data Corruption

@@ Should hostPath be used in production?
=> Generally No.

@@ Only for:
Monitoring Agents
Node Exporters
Special Use Cases

